Question 1.
I've implemented both Insertion and Merge Sort using the required mySort() and integrated all 
the functions to track comparisons and swaps. Both algorithms are fully functional.

-----------------------------------------------

Question 2: Insertion Sort Analysis
n is the number of elements.

Best Case (Already Sorted)

Comparisons:
Total comparisons: n - 1

Moves/Copies: Each pass has 2 copies
Total moves: 2(n - 1)

Time Complexity: O(n)

---------------------------------------------

Worst Case: Reverse Sorted

Comparisons:
Total comparisons: (n - 1) + (n - 2) + ... + 1
= n(n - 1)/2

Moves/Copies: Copies 2(n-1) happen every pass
Total moves: 2(n-1) + n(n - 1)/2

Time Complexity: O(n^2)

----------------------------------------------

Average Case

Comparisons:
half of worst case = n(n-1) / 4

Moves/Copies: Copies 2(n-1) happen every pass
Total Moves: 2(n-1) + n(n-1) / 4

Time Complexity:
O(n²)


---------------------------------------------
Question 3: Merge Sort Analysis
Number of levels of recursion: log2(n)

Best Case

Comparisons: nlog2(n)

Moves/Copies: Each pass has 2 copies
2n log(n)

Time Complexity: O(nlog n)

----------------------------------------------

Average Case

Comparisons: nlog2(n)

Moves/Copies: Each pass has 2 copies
2n log2(n)

Time Complexity: O(n log n)

--------------------------------------------

Worst Case

Comparisons: nlog2(n)

Moves/Copies: Each pass has 2 copies
2nlog2(n)

Time Complexity: O(n log n)
